The '''Systems Database''' is a spreadsheet database compiled by [[Jason Fry]] since [[1995]]. Its primary focus is the locations of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] mentioned in the [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]]. There is a list of planets with their systems and sectors if known, as well as clues regarding their proximity to other bodies, stellar and galactic features, and trade routes.

It has never been released on the internet or to the public, however, [[Lucasfilm]] has used the Systems Database as a reference, and [[Daniel Wallace]] and [[James Luceno]] accessed it for their [[New Jedi Order]] map. Fry and Wallace also intend on using as much of the database as possible for the [[The Essential Atlas|''Essential Atlas'']].

As of October [[2007]], Fry's database contains 3900 entries.<ref name="Blog">{{Blog|danwallace|87|3900 Planetary Systems And Counting&hellip;}}</ref> By [[2015]], the database contained 5,085 systems.<ref name="TFAoSWTEA">{{SW|subdomain=www|url=news/the-further-adventures-of-star-wars-the-essential-atlas|text=The Further Adventures of Star Wars: The Essential Atlas}}</ref>

